<div class="c230_126"> 
<div id="v230.126.1"><span class="H7892 s">A Song</span><span class="H4609 s"> of degrees</span><span class="H3068 s">. When the LORD</span><span class="H7725 s"> turned again</span><span class="H7870 s"> the captivity</span><span class="H6726 s"> of Zion</span><span class="H2492 s">, we were like them that dream</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (turned…: Heb. returned the returning)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.126.2"><span class="H6310 s">Then was our mouth</span><span class="H4390 s"> filled</span><span class="H7814 s"> with laughter</span><span class="H3956 s">, and our tongue</span><span class="H7440 s"> with singing</span><span class="H559 s">: then said</span><span class="H1471 s"> they among the heathen</span><span class="H3068 s">, The LORD</span><span class="H6213 s"> hath done</span><span class="H1431 s"> great things</span> for them. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (hath…: Heb. hath magnified to do with them)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.126.3"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H6213 s"> hath done</span><span class="H1431 s"> great things</span><span class="H8056 s"> for us; <i>whereof</i> we are glad</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.126.4"><span class="H7725 s">Turn again</span><span class="H7622 s"> our captivity</span><span class="H7622 s"> †</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H650 s">, as the streams</span><span class="H5045 s"> in the south</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.126.5"><span class="H2232 s">They that sow</span><span class="H1832 s"> in tears</span><span class="H7114 s"> shall reap</span><span class="H7440 s"> in joy</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (joy: or, singing)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.126.6"><span class="H3212 s">He that goeth</span><span class="H1980 s"> forth</span><span class="H1058 s"> and weepeth</span><span class="H5375 s">, bearing</span><span class="H4901 s"> precious</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H935 s">, shall doubtless</span><span class="H935 s"> come</span><span class="H7440 s"> again with rejoicing</span><span class="H5375 s">, bringing</span><span class="H485 s"> his sheaves</span> <i>with him</i>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (precious…: or, seed basket)</span></div></div>

